{
  "stem": "12150.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that's how the business went on.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My father was working about six, seven hours a day.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And in the evening, then he went home, as far as I remember, to eat dinner.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And after dinner, every night of the week, we went to pray and to learn the Bible, which was very, very common in those years, in most of the Eastern European cities or towns, or even in villages, if they had congregations or synagogues.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Munkacs was a town that consisted of 21,000 Jews-- about 90% Hasidic.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And at least 60% of those Jews were dealers, businesspeople.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Some of them were very, very rich, and they had maids in their homes.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Shuls, congregations-- the town had plenty.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And there were sects, factions, and no real fights.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But people belonged to whatever-- probably handed down to them from their-- their grandparents-- certain shuls.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And they belonged to them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And most of the people bought their seats outright, when they built it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They didn't rent it, like here, and pay once a year $200.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It was their seats, with their name on it-- metal plates with the name on it, about 90% of the people.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Those that did not have money, or they didn't own seats, there was tables arranged for them, with benches.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And then the shuls were open-- not like in America.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "In some shuls they have guards when they go in.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But the shuls were open to anyone who wanted to pray or to learn.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They belonged to two synagogues.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And one was the synagogue called Belz-- B-E-L-Z-- which was a subsidiary of a Polish big rabbi, or followers of a big rabbi-- a big congregation, possibly 600, 700 families.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the other congregation was not far from our house.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
